services: Miles just started in Early Intervention services through REACH (provider in Western Mass). After undergoing an assessment, he didn't meet the clinical criteria for enrollment, but the clinicians used "clinical judgement" to make him eligible for services. The issues seem to be in expressive vocabulary and language production, while language comprehension and other aspects of cognitive, social, and motor development are on track. His expressive vocabulary was deemed at the low end of the average range. The clinicians think that the expressive language delays are due to his inability to make the muscles in his face, tongue, and mouth create the sounds, and also because he's super busy and doesn't stick around long enough to stare at people's faces when they're making words.
